				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have searched the beastiary website and found that the pickings for 'Summoned Mobs' pretty much sucks for a solo mage.  The only zone I noticed any significant amount of things to kill is The Hole.  Reason I am looking for 'summoned' creatures is mainly to put some dusty spells to use and let my pet get some use of dual-wielding weapons he can proc on them.  I have no problems soloing BW/Velks/ or any number of other spots but it would be nice to actually USE some of the positive offensive measures Mages get.  Lord knows, as someone else posted, Mages are the Masters of elements and can't even get a cold-based spell ?!?! wth is up with that ?  I think I have cast my Banish Summoned line of spells about as much as I have 'Flare'.  The only use I have had of them so far is on raids where a caster with a pet is having to be taken out & it went something like this.    
<br />

<br />
Mage put your pet on mobs pet and just keep it busy while we kill main.  When we're done we'll assist you. 
<br />

<br />
Ranger .. keep eye on Mage and when his pet dies heal him till we can pull it off him ... Cleric .. mem rezz please .. Mage is gonna need it.
<br />

<br />
&lt;combat begins&gt;
<br />

<br />
"A so and so's pet staggers"
<br />
"A so and so's pet has taken xamount of non-melee damage"
<br />
"Jebartik flexes his muscles and slices thru so and so's pet like a blender"
<br />
"A so and so's pet has been slain by Jebartik"
<br />
"You begin casting"
<br />
"A so and so is bathed in fire"
<br />
"A so and so has taken 960 points of non-melee damage"
<br />

<br />
Mage !!! you are supposed to be on the pet !!!
<br />
Oh.... you already killed it ?
<br />
WOW !!!! thats one bad ass pet you have (why people never seem to stop underestimating our pets I will never know LOL)
<br />

<br />
Anyway I got WAYYY side tracked...  is there anywhere to solo summoned mobs for levels 50-57 or so ?? Thanks for any ideas.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
